Cardiff rejected big offers for Marshall last year with Arsenal among his suitors but he has been one of the most consistent goalkeepers in England's top-two divisions over recent seasons.

Norwich City's John Ruddy, Ali Al Habsi of Wigan Athletic, Sergio Romero of Sampdoria and Erwin Mulder of Feyenoord have also been mentioned.

Ujpest goalkeeper and Serbia Under 21 international Marko Dmitrovic, 22, has also been invited to come in on trial.

