West Ham United are continuing to assess possible additions to their squad.

Sturm Graz midfielder Anel Hadzic has again been offered to manager Sam Allardyce. The 25-year-old Bosnia international can play at centre back and could also provide cover for Alex Song after his call-up from Cameroon.

Bordeaux defender Ludovic Sane, a long-time target, has also been discussed again as, despite signing Doneil Henry, Allardyce wants experience for his defence in the second half of the season.

